## Auth flow

```
Login page → signInWithOtp(email)
  → User clicks magic link in email
  → GET /api/callback/auth?code=…&next=/profile
  → exchangeCodeForSession(code)
  → Redirect to /profile

Logout → signOut() → clear user cache → redirect to /login
```

## When adding user management later

1. Confirm roles model (admin vs user, or RBAC) before implementing guards
2. Decide if `profiles` table is needed alongside auth metadata
3. Admin UI belongs under a new feature module; keep invite-only flow unless registration decision changes
4. Any new public routes must be added to `isPublicRoute` in the proxy

## Do not

- Hand-write Supabase user types — use auth types from `@supabase/supabase-js` until a profiles schema exists
- Use `service_role` key in client or browser-reachable routes
- Duplicate Supabase client setup — reuse `@/lib/supabase/*` helpers
- Add hardcoded UI strings — use `next-intl`
